The paper presents a new distribution layer for Erlang that enables cloud-scale applications. It focuses on distributed programming and network topologies, which are relevant to categories such as Distributed Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Distributed Systems (cs.Distributed). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of the system under different network conditions, which is relevant to Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
